WEBVTT

1
00:00:16.083 --> 00:00:18.375
Good morning. the Gomoras!

2
00:00:18.458 --> 00:00:20.625
-It's your birthday!
-Wow!

3
00:00:20.708 --> 00:00:23.166
-Happy Birthday!
-My brother!

4
00:00:23.250 --> 00:00:26.291
Hip hip hooray! Bring out the balloons!

5
00:00:27.833 --> 00:00:29.250
Happy birthday. my brother.
Happy birthday.

6
00:00:29.333 --> 00:00:31.541
-Thank you.
-You're here now. You're here.

7
00:00:31.625 --> 00:00:34.166
-Never. Never. What?
-Getting old now. He's getting old.

8
00:00:34.250 --> 00:00:35.541
-Seriously.
-Who?

9
00:00:35.625 --> 00:00:37.958
So. tell me. brother.
What are we doing tonight?

10
00:00:38.041 --> 00:00:40.750
You know that's Joyce's thing.
She's handling it.

11
00:00:40.833 --> 00:00:42.375
-Oh. I know her very well.
-She's on top of it.

12
00:00:42.458 --> 00:00:44.583
I know she's very good at what she does.

13
00:00:44.666 --> 00:00:47.708
My boy. give me a high five
and another one.

14
00:00:47.791 --> 00:00:49.791
There we go. Eat your bread.

15
00:00:49.875 --> 00:00:53.541
Stop messing around. It's a problem.

16
00:00:53.625 --> 00:00:54.708
Ah. there we go.

17
00:00:54.791 --> 00:00:56.083
-Baby girl. are you okay?
-I'm all right.

18
00:00:56.166 --> 00:00:57.458
Good. good.

19
00:01:22.458 --> 00:01:25.375
Come on. friend. You can't compare
yourself to other people.

20
00:01:25.458 --> 00:01:27.208
-I don't know.
-Out of all people.

21
00:01:27.291 --> 00:01:30.458
you should know better
than to trust social media. man.

22
00:01:30.541 --> 00:01:33.708
We're watching these people.
and yes. they have their issues.

23
00:01:33.791 --> 00:01:35.750
but despite everything.

24
00:01:36.458 --> 00:01:41.500
there are moments when you can
actually see genuine happiness.

25
00:01:41.583 --> 00:01:45.416
I thought that we could also make it work.
but then…

26
00:01:46.458 --> 00:01:48.875
…clearly I've been fooling myself.

27
00:01:48.958 --> 00:01:52.458
-Hmm.
-I'm in the depths of hell.

28
00:01:52.541 --> 00:01:54.416
I'm on fire.

29
00:01:54.500 --> 00:01:57.833
I didn't want to tell you. but I don't
think polygamy is for everyone. friend.

30
00:01:57.916 --> 00:01:59.458
It really isn't. hey.

31
00:02:00.416 --> 00:02:02.791
I just feel like I'm in hell.

32
00:02:02.875 --> 00:02:08.333
Friend. you gave Jonasi the permission
to have his cake and eat it too.

33
00:02:08.833 --> 00:02:12.458
You know. I wish I knew
what to do about all of this.

34
00:02:12.541 --> 00:02:14.541
At this point. I don't think
there's anything you can do.

35
00:02:14.625 --> 00:02:17.708
You also went and told the whole world
that you guys are okay. right?

36
00:02:17.791 --> 00:02:19.375
No. this isn't fine.

37
00:02:19.458 --> 00:02:20.750
You can still walk away.

38
00:02:20.833 --> 00:02:22.500
I love him. Zodwa.

39
00:02:24.333 --> 00:02:25.416
It's his birthday today.

40
00:02:26.166 --> 00:02:30.583
So. maybe what we need
is just to spend time together.

41
00:02:31.333 --> 00:02:32.791
-You know?
-I can't. my friend.

42
00:02:32.875 --> 00:02:34.708
I need time.

43
00:02:34.791 --> 00:02:35.916
Yesterday. I made a decision

44
00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:39.791
to just cancel his birthday dinner
reservation at the restaurant. friend.

45
00:02:39.875 --> 00:02:43.916
His annual birthday dinner plans as well.
I just can't.

46
00:02:45.333 --> 00:02:47.125
I can't do it.

47
00:02:47.208 --> 00:02:49.000
Well. I'm proud of you.

48
00:02:49.083 --> 00:02:50.375
-You're proud?
-Mm-hmm.

49
00:02:50.458 --> 00:02:52.250
-Proud?
-Mm-hmm.

50
00:02:54.791 --> 00:02:56.000
Well done.

51
00:02:57.708 --> 00:02:59.041
I appreciate you.

52
00:03:14.833 --> 00:03:16.000
Ah.

53
00:03:16.958 --> 00:03:20.958
You see now? You see now?

54
00:03:21.041 --> 00:03:25.291
-Hmm?
-Happy birthday to you

55
00:03:25.375 --> 00:03:29.375
Happy birthday to you

56
00:03:29.875 --> 00:03:33.333
Happy birthday. dear Jo

57
00:03:33.416 --> 00:03:39.291
-Mmm. mmm. mmm.
-Happy birthday to you

58
00:03:39.375 --> 00:03:43.458
You know what. I should just
get in my car and head to you right now.

59
00:03:43.541 --> 00:03:45.166
Calm down.

60
00:03:45.250 --> 00:03:49.041
This is only just a sneak-peek.
I've got more for you tonight.

61
00:03:49.125 --> 00:03:52.000
I asked a second nanny
to help Jane with the kids.

62
00:03:52.083 --> 00:03:56.708
Uh. tonight is going to be a bit tricky

63
00:03:56.791 --> 00:03:59.750
because birthdays are Joyce's thing.

64
00:03:59.833 --> 00:04:02.833
You do understand that
it's your first birthday as my husband?

65
00:04:02.916 --> 00:04:04.416
As my official husband?

66
00:04:04.500 --> 00:04:09.916
I know. You know these past three weeks
have been very tricky.

67
00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:12.125
Let's not make things worse.

68
00:04:12.208 --> 00:04:13.791
Oh. my gosh.

69
00:04:13.875 --> 00:04:15.458
Okay. you know what?

70
00:04:17.083 --> 00:04:19.875
This coming weekend is all ours.

71
00:04:20.458 --> 00:04:21.541
Okay?

72
00:04:21.625 --> 00:04:24.250
I'll book us a place. It'll be exotic.

73
00:04:24.916 --> 00:04:27.583
We'll go to the beach
where you and I can be naked.

74
00:04:27.666 --> 00:04:30.291
You know what. Jonasi? Gomora.

75
00:04:30.375 --> 00:04:34.416
Enjoy your birthday with your wife
who you love more than anything.

76
00:04:34.500 --> 00:04:35.541
-Wow.
-Goodbye.

77
00:04:41.958 --> 00:04:43.291
Hmm.

78
00:04:48.958 --> 00:04:50.625
Joyce?

79
00:04:52.416 --> 00:04:53.958
Joyce.

80
00:04:55.208 --> 00:04:57.708
Hmm. you've finally arrived. Hello.

81
00:04:59.666 --> 00:05:01.166
Hello.

82
00:05:01.666 --> 00:05:02.791
You're drinking?

83
00:05:05.500 --> 00:05:06.750
Hold on… …what…

84
00:05:08.500 --> 00:05:09.875
What day is it today?

85
00:05:10.833 --> 00:05:12.041
It's Thursday.

86
00:05:13.625 --> 00:05:14.625
What?

87
00:05:22.583 --> 00:05:23.666
Why did you call me back home?

88
00:05:23.750 --> 00:05:28.291
Oh. yes.
The toilet in the en-suite isn't working.

89
00:05:29.416 --> 00:05:30.416
Why didn't you call the plumber?

90
00:05:30.500 --> 00:05:32.041
And why should I call a plumber?

91
00:05:32.125 --> 00:05:33.500
I won't stay here.

92
00:05:34.458 --> 00:05:36.250
Being miserable like you
and drinking alcohol.

93
00:05:36.333 --> 00:05:39.958
-Now I'm miserable.
-I didn't ask for a second wife. You did.

94
00:05:40.583 --> 00:05:41.875
Joyce. I've apologized.

95
00:05:42.458 --> 00:05:44.208
I followed all your rules.

96
00:05:45.041 --> 00:05:46.333
What do you want from me?

97
00:05:47.000 --> 00:05:48.333
What do you want?

98
00:05:53.625 --> 00:05:55.250
What are we doing tonight?

99
00:05:59.583 --> 00:06:01.000
I don't know. hey.

100
00:06:01.083 --> 00:06:03.750
but. uh. the night is still young.

101
00:06:04.958 --> 00:06:09.916
I'm in no rush.
I'm just chilling. I'ma relax.

102
00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:11.750
