-I don't have an appetite.

189
00:09:54.291 --> 00:09:56.250
Okay. You know what?

190
00:09:56.875 --> 00:10:00.083
I can tell we all don't have an appetite.

191
00:10:00.166 --> 00:10:02.875
Why don't we ask Ntombi
to make us some dessert?

192
00:10:02.958 --> 00:10:04.541
Maybe she can serve us some ice cream?

193
00:10:05.125 --> 00:10:06.333
How's that?

194
00:10:06.416 --> 00:10:08.708
Guys.

195
00:10:09.875 --> 00:10:11.250
Guys.

196
00:10:11.333 --> 00:10:13.541
Is this how things are going to be?

197
00:10:13.625 --> 00:10:16.916
Being a family that doesn't talk?
Just be down and depressed like this?

198
00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:18.416
Come on.

199
00:10:19.541 --> 00:10:22.250
My baby.
you're off to varsity in two weeks.

200
00:10:22.333 --> 00:10:24.875
I'm sure there's lots of things
you'd like us to talk about.

201
00:10:25.750 --> 00:10:27.208
No?

202
00:10:28.750 --> 00:10:31.916
Okay. my boy. what about you?

203
00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:36.291
Surely there has to be some sort of
office gossip that's been going around

204
00:10:36.375 --> 00:10:38.000
that we can talk about?

205
00:10:38.083 --> 00:10:40.000
Sorry. Mom.

206
00:10:40.666 --> 00:10:43.791
Sorry that we can't pretend
as if nothing happened.

207
00:10:43.875 --> 00:10:47.458
I just wish our family
could go back to how it used to be.

208
00:10:47.541 --> 00:10:49.875
-And be a normal family.
-Normal?

209
00:10:50.458 --> 00:10:53.666
-He hid an entire family.
-He's still your father. He's your dad.

210
00:10:53.750 --> 00:10:55.583
-Menzi.
-He still deserves your respect.

211
00:10:55.666 --> 00:10:59.750
I wonder what lies he's been feeding you
when you guys are cruising to work.

212
00:10:59.833 --> 00:11:00.875
Stop!

213
00:11:03.458 --> 00:11:04.625
Listen here.

214
00:11:05.416 --> 00:11:09.958
I'm not going to sit here and watch
you both rip each other into shreds

215
00:11:10.041 --> 00:11:13.833
over a man that's out there
living his best life!

216
00:11:14.750 --> 00:11:15.833
Do you hear me?

217
00:11:20.416 --> 00:11:22.625
Celebrating his birthday without us?

218
00:11:23.666 --> 00:11:24.791
Must be nice.

219
00:11:24.875 --> 00:11:25.958
Yes. Mpume.

220
00:11:27.375 --> 00:11:29.458
It's your father's birthday today.

221
00:11:29.541 --> 00:11:30.958
But you see this.

222
00:11:31.541 --> 00:11:33.333
what we have here…

223
00:11:35.208 --> 00:11:37.416
it's our peace. Right here.

224
00:11:38.916 --> 00:11:40.458
And I am not…

225
00:11:43.125 --> 00:11:45.916
I'm not going to allow him
to take that from us.

226
00:11:46.541 --> 00:11:47.666
Not anymore.

227
00:11:51.500 --> 00:11:52.916
Not anymore.

228
00:11:54.750 --> 00:11:57.916
Happy birthday to you

229
00:11:58.000 --> 00:12:00.875
Happy birthday to you

230
00:12:00.958 --> 00:12:04.208
-Happy birthday. dear Daddy
-Happy birthday. dear Husband

231
00:12:05.375 --> 00:12:08.250
-Happy birthday to you
-Hip hip!

232
00:12:08.333 --> 00:12:09.500
Hooray!

233
00:12:09.583 --> 00:12:11.541
Hip hip! Hooray!

234
00:12:11.625 --> 00:12:13.375
-Here's your cake…
-Mm-hmm.

235
00:12:13.458 --> 00:12:15.000
…so blow your candles and make a wish.

236
00:12:15.625 --> 00:12:17.166
My goodness.

237
00:12:17.250 --> 00:12:18.625
-Forty-five.
-Yes.

238
00:12:18.708 --> 00:12:20.666
You're old now.

239
00:12:21.250 --> 00:12:23.791
There we go.

240
00:12:23.875 --> 00:12:25.916
